    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774632805824",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "./my-notebook.ipynb",
      "x": -523,
      "y": 677,
      "width": 529,
      "height": 750,
      "nodeLabel": "J3"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774880170104",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# How cusum is applied\r\n\r\nPipeline order (from source): \r\nsignals → BasicProcessor → trades → minimal_return filter → CUSUM filter → weights → label\r\n\r\n## CUSUM mechanics:                                                                                                         \r\nthreshold(t) = vol(t) × cusum_threshold × close(t)    [in price/dollar units]\r\naccumulate D[close] until sum > threshold → fire event, reset \r\n→ trade only survives if its entry_time hits a CUSUM event \r\n\r\nFor cusum_threshold=0.05, volatility_timeframe=4h:\r\n- vol ≈ 1% of price → threshold ≈ 1% × 0.05 × price = 0.05% of price \r\n- At BTC = $64k → threshold ≈ $31\r\n\r\nThe real finding — CUSUM is nearly inactive at 15min\r\n  CUSUM fires every 1-2 bars at 15min — the threshold ($31) is smaller than a single typical bar move ($81), so it resets\r\n\r\n  and re-fires constantly. It's barely filtering anything (80% of bars are \"events\")                                                                                                                          \r\nNeither timeframe is doing meaningful CUSUM filtering (73–80% pass rates), but 15min is worse. For CUSUM to be a useful   \r\n\r\nfilter you'd want ~20–30% pass rate — which would require raising cusum_threshold to roughly 0.3–0.5 at 15min.\r\n",
      "x": -61,
      "y": -2986,
      "width": 1103,
      "height": 358,
      "nodeLabel": "N4"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774880609230",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Targets generation for 15 min \r\n\r\n- validation of targets \r\n",
      "x": -1065,
      "y": -2986,
      "width": 444,
      "height": 96,
      "nodeLabel": "N5"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774958487524",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Simplest formula\r\n$$\r\n\\begin{equation*}\r\nd x_{i}=a_{i}(\\mathbf{x}, t) d t+b_{i \\alpha}(\\mathbf{x}, t) \\delta W_{\\alpha}, \\tag{6.4}\r\n\\end{equation*}\r\n$$",
      "x": -1049,
      "y": -2628,
      "width": 413,
      "height": 162,
      "nodeLabel": "N6"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774961140308",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Note 2",
      "x": -523,
      "y": -2594,
      "width": 462,
      "height": 95,
      "nodeLabel": "N9"
    },
    {
      "id": "node-1774965277833",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Feller process\r\n\r\n$$\r\ndx = -\\beta \\cdot (x - \\alpha) dt + \\sigma \\sqrt{x} \\delta W(1)\r\n$$\r\n",
      "x": -1053,
      "y": -2327,
      "width": 427,
      "height": 184,
      "nodeLabel": "N8"
    },
